<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="533" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1084,1432]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1119,1144]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[336,402,1119,1144]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 8" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1982,2005]" captionTargetBox="[197,1379,232,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[152,1435,193,2007]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 8. Dorsal habitus of Limnophora species: 5. Limnophora parallelifrons Emden. 6. Limnophora perfidodes Emden. 7. Limnophora simulans Stein. 8. Limnophora translucida Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242397/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) Presutural spots separated posteriorly or wholly fused, sometimes narrowly connected with the presutural band on median line, but not extending on to postpronotum as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1290,1156,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Limnophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavibasis">
<emphasis box="[1146,1290,1156,1180]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">L. flavibasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; postsutural dorsocentrals 4; mid femur with 2 preapical setae; mid tibia with 2 posterior setae; costal spine not distinct; basal abdominal segments yellow; sternite 5 much longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[861,959,1228,1253]" captionStart="FIGURES 104 – 119" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1943,1966]" captionTargetBox="[187,1402,206,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[179,1408,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 104 – 119. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 104 – 107. Limnophora spinifera Stein. 108 – 111. Limnophora stragula (Séguy). 112 – 115. Limnophora translucida Stein. 116 – 119. Limnophora trigemina Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1084,1432]" box="[199,1224,1263,1288]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">
Terminalia. Cercal plate and surstylus as in 
<figureCitation box="[688,838,1263,1288]" captionStart="FIGURES 104 – 119" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1943,1966]" captionTargetBox="[187,1402,206,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[179,1408,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 104 – 119. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 104 – 107. Limnophora spinifera Stein. 108 – 111. Limnophora stragula (Séguy). 112 – 115. Limnophora translucida Stein. 116 – 119. Limnophora trigemina Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Figs 113-114</figureCitation>
. Aedeagal complex as in 
<figureCitation box="[1124,1220,1263,1288]" captionStart="FIGURES 104 – 119" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1943,1966]" captionTargetBox="[187,1402,206,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[179,1408,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 104 – 119. Sternite 5; cercal plate and surstyli in dorsal view; epandrium, cercal plate and surstyli in lateral view; aedeagus in lateral view: 104 – 107. Limnophora spinifera Stein. 108 – 111. Limnophora stragula (Séguy). 112 – 115. Limnophora translucida Stein. 116 – 119. Limnophora trigemina Stein." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242404/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1084,1432]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424565255" collectionCode="BMNH" location="A" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="A" typeStatus="paratype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1300,1325]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">Notes.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[280,300,1300,1324]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">A</collectingRegion>
long series of males and females in the 
<collectionCode box="[751,839,1301,1324]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">BMNH</collectionCode>
. One male dissected and illustrated. The morphology of the male terminalia is identical with that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Paterson, 1955" authorityName="Paterson" authorityYear="1955" box="[707,1024,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Limnophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis box="[707,842,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">L. terrestris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[853,1024,1335,1360]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" refString="Paterson, H. E. (1955) Two new species of Limnophora (Diptera: Muscidae) related to Limnophora translucida Stein. Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 18, 137 - 143." type="journal article" year="1955">Paterson, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1042,1140,1336,1360]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">paratype</typeStatus>
male seen and one male dissected), and the synonymy of these two species is proposed herein, with 
<taxonomicName box="[1018,1151,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Limnophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis box="[1018,1151,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">L. terrestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being ranked as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[291,448,1408,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Limnophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="translucida">
<emphasis box="[291,448,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">L. translucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[464,567,1407,1432]" pageId="32" pageNumber="533">syn. nov.</emphasis>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
